[ProMED-mail thanks Dr Jan Clement for his comments. Dr Clement makes the important point, as he has previously, that _Seoul hantavirus_, or SEOV, infection may be misdiagnosed as leptospirosis, since serious, potentially life-threatening complications of leptospirosis that include renal failure, liver disease, and pneumonia can mimic the clinical manifestations of SEOV infection. The potential for misdiagnosis will not be resolved until routine laboratory tests are done to differentiate between them. Dr Clement also reminds us that more than one pathogen may be responsible for the disease outbreak that occurred since brown rats are the reservoir for both SEOV and _Leptospira_. - Mod.ML

HealthMap/ProMED map of Australia: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=8380596,285]
